}}'''Axess Vision Technology''' is a start up company and [[manufacturer]] of medical devices, mainly  [[endoscope]]s. It is headquartered in Saint Pierre des Corps,France.It is competing with Ambu and Single Use Surgical Ltd to develop the world first generation of disposable endoscopes.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Brosky |first1=John |last2= |first2= |year=2009 |title=Three EU companies vying to launch single use endoscope |journal=Medical Device Daily |volume=13 |issue= |pages= |publisher= |doi= |url= |accessdate= }}</ref> These companies are responding to a market need of getting rid of cross contamination from flexible endoscopes, the latter ranked third in the ECRI 2011 top 10 Health Hazards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ecri.org/Forms/Documents/Top_10_Health_Tech_Hazards_2011.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-04-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724160457/https://www.ecri.org/Forms/Documents/Top_10_Health_Tech_Hazards_2011.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-24 |df= }}</ref> Even when endoscopes are thoroughly cleaned, there remains a risk of infection of 1%. Therefore, these endoscopes are designed to be used on one patient only before being incinerated.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=|first1=|last2= |first2=|year=2011|title=100 start up où investir santé et biologie|journal=Challenges|volume=|issue=256|pages= |publisher= |doi= |url=http://www.challenges.fr/magazine/encouverture/0256.035397/|accessdate=2011-05-13 }}</ref>

